Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and thinly sliced). Grate the @Mature Cheddar cheese{90%g}.

Halve any large @Cauliflower Florets{300%g}. Pop the florets onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1} for the crumb, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, when boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{1/2} and stir through to stop it sticking together. While the pasta cooks, pop the @Panko Breadcrumbs{50%g} into a #medium bowl{} and add the olive oil for the crumb. Season with salt and pepper, mix together, then set aside.

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @oil{1.5} for the roux and the onion. Cook until softened and golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the @Plain Flour{24%g} and cook until it forms a paste-like roux, ~{1-2%minutes}. Gradually, stir in the @water{250%ml} for the sauce and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}, stirring continuously. Mix in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the Cheddar to the sauce and stir until melted. Taste and add salt and pepper if needed. Stir the cooked pasta and cauliflower through the sauce with a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Spoon into a #medium-sized ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle the crumbs evenly over the top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the pasta bakes, pop the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} into a medium bowl with the @olive oil{2} for the dressing and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Once the pasta is cooked, add the @Wild Rocket{40%g} to the dressing and toss to coat. Serve the cauliflower rigatoni cheese with the salad alongside. Enjoy!